OL,3,CThe Single Justice Procedure: What is
OL,4,Cit and why are there calls for reform?
OL,6,FMost cases are heard in private, as
OL,7,Funder SJP when a defendant pleads
OL,8,Fguilty, they do not have to go to
OL,9,Fcourt - unless they want to.
OL,11,FThose accused of offences receive a
OL,12,FSingle Justice Procedure Notice in the
OL,13,Fpost - this contains details like the
OL,14,Fcharge, how to enter a plea and a
OL,15,Fchance for defendants to submit
OL,16,Fmitigating circumstances.
OL,18,FThese mitigating circumstances offer
OL,19,Fthe opportunity for defendants to
OL,20,Fprovide reasons as to why they might
OL,21,Fhave committed the offence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/21
