OL,3,CThe Single Justice Procedure: What is
OL,4,Cit and why are there calls for reform?
OL,6,FThey are read by the magistrate who
OL,7,Freviews the case, and are taken into
OL,8,Fconsideration when they decide its
OL,9,Foutcome. However, the prosecutor -
OL,10,Fsuch as the DVLA or TV Licensing - is
OL,11,Fnot required to read these.
OL,13,FA magistrate can adjourn a case and
OL,14,Fask the prosecution to review the
OL,15,Fmitigating circumstances if they
OL,16,Fbelieve it is not in the public
OL,17,Finterest to prosecute. They can also
OL,18,Freduce the penalty imposed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
