OL,3,CThe Single Justice Procedure: What is
OL,4,Cit and why are there calls for reform?
OL,6,FThese were independently reviewed by a
OL,7,Fpanel of four criminal barristers.
OL,9,FThey found it was not in the public
OL,10,Finterest to prosecute almost three
OL,11,Fquarters (74%) of these cases, and
OL,12,Fthat nearly one in three (58%) would
OL,13,Flikely have resulted in a different
OL,14,Foutcome if the defendant had access to
OL,15,Fa lawyer in open court.
OL,17,FWe asked each of the lawyers for their
OL,18,Fthoughts on the current system and the
OL,19,Fcases they reviewed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
