OL,3,CThe Single Justice Procedure: What is
OL,4,Cit and why are there calls for reform?
OL,6,FDonal Lawler, barrister at 187
OL,7,FChambers, said: "If a procedure for
OL,8,Fdealing with offences, no matter how
OL,9,Fminor, has this many potential
OL,10,Finjustices it is not fair,
OL,11,Ftransparent, or rigorous. It is simply
OL,12,Fnot fit for purpose.
OL,14,F"The majority of the cases I looked at
OL,15,Fwould all have had different outcomes
OL,16,Fif either a prosecution lawyer or a
OL,17,Fdefence lawyer had looked at it before
OL,18,Fit reached the magistrates. A
OL,19,F'conveyer belt' has no place in the
OL,20,Fcriminal justice system."
